{
  "title": "Deploying CLI Tools Using FastAPI with Python 3.12+",
  "summary": "This guide explains how to create and deploy a command-line interface (CLI) tool using FastAPI, a modern web framework for building APIs in Python 3.12+.",

  "key_points": [
    "FastAPI can be used to build not only REST APIs but also CLI tools.",
    "We will create a FastAPI application with a single endpoint accepting command-line arguments.",
    "The FastAPI app will be deployed as a standalone executable using the `uvicorn` and `pypa-auto-py-to-exe` packages.",

  ],

  "code_examples": [
    {
      "language": "python",
      "code": "```\n\
import uvicorn\n\
from fastapi import FastAPI, CommandLineInput, FastAPIRequest\n\
app = FastAPI()\n\
\n@app.on_event('startup')\ndef startup():\n    arg_parser = uvicorn.Config.for_argv('__main__')\n    uvicorn.run(app, host='127.0.0.1', port=8000, reload=True, log_level=\"info\", server=\"uvicorn.workers.UvicornWorker\", extra_arguments=[arg_parser.args[1:]])\n\n@app.get('/{command}')\ndef command(command: str = CommandLineInput()):\n    print(f'You entered command: {command}')\n```"
    },
    {
      "language": "bash",
      "code": "```\n\
pip install fastapi uvicorn pypa-auto-py-to-exe\n\
python -m uvicorn main:app --host 127.0.0.1 --port 8000 --reload --log-level info --app main\n```"
    },
    {
      "language": "bash",
      "code": "```\n\
pypa-auto-py-to-exe -c 'uvicorn main:app' -o my_cli_tool --base-dir=. --include='*.py,__pycache__/*' --exclude='venv,*__pycache__/*' --additional-args='--log-level info --host 127.0.0.1 --port 8000' --icon-path icon.ico\n```"
    }
  ],

  "version_notes": [
    "FastAPI v0.76.0 or later is required.",
    "Python 3.12+ is recommended."
  ],

  "caveats": [
    "The example provided here uses a simple command-line argument parser and might not cover all use cases for CLI tools.",
    "This guide assumes you have already set up your development environment with FastAPI, uvicorn, and pypa-auto-py-to-exe."
  ]
}
